comments.body:
I _think_ this fix is verified, but need input from [~vasya] to make sure I have it correct.

When I provide the -Xmx5G on the eucalyptus-cloud command line (inside the /etc/init.d/eucalyptus-cloud script at line 278), I see that log output showing the user did not set heap size, such as: 

{code:java}
User did not set heap size. Setting it automatically to 4GB base on total memory of 8244002816 bytes
{code}

Yet it doesn't show what the heap size is in the log file (maybe you could add a statement that shows the user defined heap size).  I believe I'm verifying the heap size when I use -v (verbose) it shows the maximum value in parentheses during GC output such as:

{code:java}
.3.914: [GC3.914: [ParNew: 295249K->27232K(306688K), 0.0442730 secs] 295249K->36935K(4160256K), 0.0443310 secs] [Times: user=0.15 sys=0.00, real=0.05 secs] 
..
6.013: [GC6.013: [ParNew: 297941K->25524K(306688K), 0.0344190 secs] 307645K->39132K(4160256K), 0.0344960 secs] [Times: user=0.12 sys=0.00, real=0.04 secs] 
{code}

The pertinent value is in parenthesis, 4160256K which is 4G, and when I set it to 5G using -Xmx5G it shows 5GB (or 5208832K):

{code:java}
42.035: [GC42.035: [ParNew: 295767K->30211K(306688K), 0.0326470 secs] 548953K->290149K(5208832K), 0.0328220 secs] [Times: user=0.12 sys=0.00, real=0.03 secs] 
43.098: [GC43.098: [ParNew: 302851K->33356K(306688K), 0.0329570 secs] 562789K->312586K(5208832K), 0.0331300 secs] [Times: user=0.12 sys=0.01, real=0.04 secs] 
{code}

[~vasya] do you agree this is validated now?  If not please indicate how I should be setting and checking the heap size.  Also, please consider updating eucalyptus-bootstrap.c to also emit the heap size that was set by the user, not just the situation when the user does not set the heap size.

Fix verified.

Thank you for the explanation [~vasya].

Using these settings in eucalyptus.conf:


{code:java}
[root@d-23 ~]# grep CLOUD_OPTS /etc/eucalyptus/eucalyptus.conf
CLOUD_OPTS="-Xms5G -Xmx6G --debug"
{code}

I was able to see the setting in the startup.log:

{code:java}
2015-10-13 10:25:11 DEBUG 0821 User defined heap size is 6442450944 bytes
{code}

When heap size is not specified, half the memory on the system is used:


{code:java}
User did not set heap size. Setting it automatically to 4GB base on total memory of 8244002816 bytes
[root@d-23 ~]# grep MemTotal /proc/meminfo
MemTotal:        8050784 kB
{code}

